		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Hi Scott! I have a followup question on hand stretches and technique. I am recently experiencing some left wrist pain and it seems to be due to my playing. After research, I gather that apparently I need to really keep my wrist straight. The pain hasn&#8217;t fully gone away after trying to do that but it seems that it&#8217;s been helping. But the issue is that keeping my wrist straight limits my technique quite a bit (many more shifts for instance as you mentioned in this episode). I have noticed that your left wrist is usually not very straight (I think I used to bend my wrist as much as you do) so I was wondering if there is something you do to prevent the pain. It will be great if you can generally comment on this whole bent vs. straight wrist issue. </p>
